president clinton in vancouver that he would look into individual case involve continue restriction on emigration from russium by address such issue thi review can help strengthen the bond of trust and partnership between the and russium and between the and the other new independent state review of cocom it be also time to consider expeditiously with america ally the future of another cold war institution the coordinating committee for multilateral export control cocom the united state ha begin a thorough review of how to reorient export control to the post-cold war world in which russium be no longer view a a potential adversary but a a potential ally in combat the proliferation of sensitive technology step to improve the security relationship the president also ha take step to move ahead on a range of effort discuss in vancouver that can strengthen security and improve my security relationship with the russian and the other state accelerated deactivation of nuclear weapon in vancouver the two president discuss accelerate the proces of deactivate nuclear strategic system schedule for elimination under the start i treaty president clinton ha direct the department of defense to complete thi proces well in advance of the seven year reduction period outline in start i in addition the united state together with russium and the other relevant state of the former soviet union will be explore program under nunn-lugar to help them to accelerate thi proces multilateral test ban the two president agree at vancouver that negotiation on a multilateral nuclear test ban should commence at an early date and that the two government would consult with each other accordingly the united state look forward to begin consultation with russium my ally and other state on the specific issue relate to thi negotiation the united state expect to start thi consultative proces within the next two month detargeting the two president also begin a dialogue on the issue of nuclear target at vancouver a the united state and russium move into a new relationship of strategic partnership there be a need to reexamine many of the assumption and mean employ in the past to safeguard security against a nuclear adversary the administration be begin a comprehensive review of measure that could enhance strategic stability include recent proposal for detargeting nuclear missile other measure to create a new security relationship in response to the incident involve a collision between u and russian submarine last month secretary aspin will be ready to discus way to avoid such incident in the future with russian defense minister grachev during hi visit to the united state in late may secretary aspin will also be prepare to move forward with defense minister grachev in may to develop a combine train program between my two military force and to prepare for joint exercise in peacekeeping such a that authorize by the un security council the united state look forward to broaden such train and exercise to include other peacekeeping contributor in order to improve inter-operability readines and plan for multilateral peacekeeping operation the u and russium be work together to convene a may ministerial meeting of the un security council to discus proposal for enhance the un peacekeeping capability and to move consideration of the secretary-general agenda for peace from the discussion to the implementation phase the be also work with the russian to focu specifically on improvement in the finance and management of un operation the purpose of these initiative will be to cooperate on peacekeeping for my participation in un or csce sponsor action multilateral and bilateral partnership with reform finally the administration continue to move ahead on a range of initiative aim at strike a partnership with economic and political reformer throughout russium and the other state the administration be continue work with my partner to assemble the package of multilateral assistance that secretary